\begin_layout Section
Concerns: isolation, neglect, exclusion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As mentioned above, three concerns motivate this paper.
 They are: (1) the isolation of heterodox economics and geographical political
 economy from each other, (2) the neglect of land rent on both sides of
 this gap, and (3) the almost complete exclusion of ground rent from the
 heterodox economics literature on the circuit of capital and, conversely,
 the almost complete exclusion of consideration of the circuit of capital
 from the literature on ground rent in geographical political economy.
 This section covers all three in some detail.
\end_layout

